The paper deals with machine learning, specifically lifelong learning and neural networks. The focus is on image data, which suggests the paper could belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses catastrophic forgetting, which is a common problem in machine learning, and proposes a solution using tensor quantization. This suggests the paper could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of natural language understanding for interactive learning, which suggests it could belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper's focus on robotic agents suggests it could belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses visual question answering, which suggests it could also belong to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category.
